commit.message: test: Wait for the log file to contain a port number

test: Move removal of SMTP AUTH response file into calling script

This might help resolve a race condition, where the protocol module
exits, and so allows the next response to be written to the file, before
the rm is done.
Bump copyright year to 2018
Bump version to 2.2
test: Add missing authtest-smtp.sh to EXTRA_DIST
doc: Fix extraneous -inject in DIAGRAM

lib/fdbuf: Fix compatibility issue with gnutls 3.6

gnutls_record_recv can return GNUTLS_E_AGAIN if the data isn't ready
immediately, so we need to check for that and try again. gnutls 3.6
exposed this problem, but it probably could happen in other
circumstances.
test: Drop failing inject blank name, behavior changed in 8d562609
test: Fix smtp-auth test causing cleanup failures

inject: Use the username as the default full name

This helps distinguish system sent messages when the MTA rewrites the
address (as does GMail, for example).

Fixes #52
send: Simplify filename logging slightly

send: Don't bounce rejected bounce messages

Thanks to Fejes József <jozsef.fejes@gmail.com> for pointing out this
failure mode.

test: Fix handling of cleaning up failed tests

If a test fails, we want the test harness to leave the evidence around.
The exit_cleanup function wasn't handling this properly and always
removed the temporary files, including logs.

protocols/smtp: Fix treating auth failure as a permanent failure

A typo in the SMTP configuration would cause messages to be rejected due
to the AUTH command being failed. This would result in password typos
causing messages to be bounced.

This change adds a new temporary error code specifically for
authentication failures, which will result in retries (with backoff)
instead of bounces.

Thanks to Fejes József <jozsef.fejes@gmail.com> for identifying this
problem.

This also adds tests for SMTP AUTH which had been missing.

sendmail: Fix compile error with GCC older than 4.9

cli_main contains a variable-length array that is initialized to the
constant {0}. This extension to the C++ standard is not present in older
versions of GCC, so replace it here with a memset.

Fixes #51
Bump date in README
Bump copyright year to 2017
lib/cli++: Fix build breakages from previous patch to cli++
NEWS: Add more notes and thanks
doc: Add man pages for mailq and nullmailer-smtpd
NEWS: Add note about previous time fix

On architectures where the type (time_t) resolves to (ulong),
command line arguments to 'dsn' are not processed correctly. The
(void) pointer passed to lib/cli++/main.cc is cast to
(unsigned int) instead of (ulong). On 64-bit little endian
architectures such as amd64 this is not readily apparent as long
as the higher bits were initialized, but it causes grave errors
on big-endian architectures such as Debian's powerpc or s390x.

This patch processes the timestamps given on the command line
correctly.
